The European Union changes the rules for obtaining the visa
People must go to the Visa Applicants Service centres before interviewing them in the Consular Section; the cost of waiting will be reduced.
As of 10 January 2011, the procedure for the treatment of visas at the United States Embassy and consulates will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will have to present themselves to the Visa Applicants Service Centres (ASC) before their interview in the Consular Section.
ASC staff will take the applicant's biometric information, which will be revised by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will bring certain benefits to the applicants, including the following:
The total cost of treating the visa will be lower, no longer will it be necessary to make a payment for a meeting, another payment for the treatment of the visa and another for the mail service to deliver the document.
The diplomat will make a unique payment that will cover the three services.
The current rate will remain the same: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 in the case of visas requested (including temporary workers visas) and $390 in the case of commercial and investor visas.
People who wish to renew their visa will not have to present themselves for an interview with the Consular Representative, they will only present themselves to the nearest CSC where they will present the documents and their fingerprints will be taken.
Due to the fact that biometric information will be taken into the CBSA, applicants wishing to meet for a second meeting to be interviewed in the Consular Section will remain there less time than before.
Similarly, visa applicants in the Consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the additional $26 service fee.
For further information on the new procedure for requesting the visa, please visit the following page: http://mexico.usebassy.gov/bolettes/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
